      "name": "Mesh convergence study — three-level Richardson extrapolation",
      "description": "A three-level structured mesh refinement study was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at the nominal operating point (2500 RPM, 5 L/min). Grid convergence index (GCI) for the hemolysis index QoI was computed as 3.2 % on the fine mesh, below the 5 % acceptance criterion. Richardson-extrapolated hemolysis index: 0.0041. Observed order of accuracy p = 1.94, consistent with second-order spatial discretization.",
