      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-head validation across operating envelope",
      "description": "Differential pressure head (ΔP) was predicted by CFD and compared against manufacturer test-bench measurements at seven flow rates (3–9 L/min) at 2500 RPM and 3500 RPM. Mean signed error: −1.8 %; RMS error: 3.1 %. Sensitivity analysis on turbulence model constants (k-ω SST Cμ ±10 %) was performed via design-of-experiments to bound numerical uncertainty on ΔP.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
