      "name": "Turbulence model sensitivity study (k-ω SST vs. RSM)",
      "description": "Two turbulence closures — k-ω SST and Reynolds Stress Model (RSM) — were applied to the pump geometry at the nominal VAD operating point. Hemolysis index predictions differed by 9.2 % between models. The k-ω SST result was selected as the primary prediction based on superior agreement with PIV velocity data. Uncertainty contribution from turbulence model form was estimated via the Eca-Hoekstra method and included in the combined uncertainty budget.",
