      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (normalized index of hemolysis) must be directly mappable to the clinical acceptance criterion without intermediate surrogates.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the regulatory QoI specified in FDA guidance for blood-contacting devices. CFD outputs are post-processed using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model to yield NIH directly. No surrogate mapping is required. Relevance is confirmed at the highest applicable gradation. Achieved level equals required level."
